item.title: [HIVE-22863] Commit compaction txn if it is opened but compaction is skipped
item.description: Currently if a table does not have enough directories to compact, compaction is skipped and the compaction is either (a) marked ready for cleaning or (b) marked compacted. However, the txn the compaction runs in is never committed, it remains open, so TXNS and TXN_COMPONENTS will never be cleared of information about the attempted compaction.
item.summary: Commit compaction txn if it is opened but compaction is skipped

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.
